      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>My favorite ploy with cell phone users in public places (Op-Ed, July 5) is to get in on the conversation. If sitting or in line, I look at the Talker intently as if he were having his conversation with me.</p>
        <p>If he makes a date -- ''I'll see you at 3'' -- I say to him, ''Can't make it at 3, how about 4?'' I get a dirty look, but Talker generally slinks away.</p>
        <p>RICHARD A. POEDTKE  Vista, Calif., July 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
